<p>I render the time stamp of a post in a jekyll based site like this:</p>  <pre><code>{{ post.date | date: "%Y%m%dT%H%M" }}00Z </code></pre>  <p>I now try to render the <code>post.date + 3hours</code> like this</p>  <pre><code>{{ post.date + 3/24 | date: "%Y%m%dT%H%M" }}00Z </code></pre>  <p>While jekyll seems to parse this just fine, the result is not changed at all (still displays the <code>post.date</code> not <code>post.date + 3hours</code>)</p>  <p>So how do I add 3 hours to the <code>post.date</code>?</p>  <p>Note: this is for creating ics files for events so post.date is the start date and time and the end date and time is 3 hours later.</p>